But there are still some mysteries left to solve from this illustrious period - did a cowboy really shoot and kill a pterodactyl? Is there really a mine full of gold just waiting to be discovered? Here's 10 Mysteries of the Wild West.

"I'm gonna take my horse to the old town road/I'm gonna ride til I can't know more". Did Lil Nas X actually succeed in this western endeavour? I suppose we will never know. There are many other mysteries to come out of the West, though - mysterious about pterodactyls, Butch Cassidy, lost mines of gold and a ship that's wound up in the desert. xbjb1rNKOIE.title: 10 Murder Mysteries With Shocking Conclusions
xbjb1rNKOIE.description:
Some homicide cases and murder mysteries have even more GOBSMACKING endings & conclusions than any movie or TV show could have. From the victim not being dead to a real life cannibal being set free, here are some of the most insane investigations ever, with 10 murder mysteries with SHOCKING conclusions.

Every good murder story needs a shocking ending - something that you'd never expect, like the butler did it or the detective did it or they all did it. Sometimes you'd be forgiven for thinking that they're far-fetched at times, but real life is often stranger than fiction. That's exactly the case here, in fact. If, for instance, a movie revealed that a MOOSE was the real culprit, or that a stamp (or lack thereof) revealed the true killer; you would surely cry codswallop. But no, these things really happened - and here are eight more murder mysteries with shocking conclusions.

9) MOOSE MURDER (1:12)
8) WHAT'S THE BEEF? (2:09)
7) GUMBALLERS (3:04)
6) BAD COP (4:00)
5) STAMPED SUSPECT (5:03)

nDnJE9kexpM.title: Will 2060 Be The End Of The World? | Insane Theories About The Apocalypse
nDnJE9kexpM.description:
Theories of a potential apocalypse have been flowing pretty much since the dawn of time itself. Some of them, though, are more out there than others. From nanobots completely wiping us out all the way to Ragnarok and a black hole or two in between, here are 10 Insane Theories About The Apocalypse.

The End Times. The End of Days. The Grand Finale. It goes by many different names but the fact of the matter is that we can only theorise on what's coming, and some have some.. extreme predictions. The Norse theory of Ragnarok, for example, where the Gods absolutely rip each other to shreds all over the Earth. The Gray Goo theory says that self-replicating robots will pretty much suffocate us all. There were even theories of Jesus Christ riding on a comet to warn people of incoming armageddon. But here are the 10 of the most out there theories on our apocalypse ever - all compiled in a list. You're most welcome!

Will Coronavirus be the next apocalypse? Find out in our video all about COVID-19 here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DlnLJDPVBYw

iDo1IXNIEJU.description:
